My strongest recommendation

At this stage, stop adding major modules.

You now have the blueprint for an enterprise platform that is broad enough to support banks, NBFCs, insurance companies, fintechs, and even non-financial enterprises.

The next phase should focus on turning this blueprint into engineering artifacts:

Reference Architecture (service boundaries and domain ownership)
Canonical Data Model (shared enterprise entities)
Enterprise Event Catalog (standardized event contracts)
Design System (UI components, layouts, accessibility)
Platform SDKs (backend and frontend)
Engineering Playbooks (coding standards, testing, observability, security)
Implementation Roadmap with phased releases

Those deliverables will determine whether ARTH.OS becomes a maintainable enterprise platform or an ever-growing collection of features.